name: R4B-Binary-R5-Binary
title: Concept map to convert a FHIR R4B Binary into FHIR R5

element.display: Pure binary content defined by a format other than FHIR

target.display: Pure binary content defined by a format other than FHIR
target.comment: R4B `Binary` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary`
R4B `Binary.contentType` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.contentType` - contentType using http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/mimetypes is exempted and assumed equivalent
R4B `Binary.data` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.data`
R4B `Binary.id` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.id`

element.display: A set of rules under which this content was created

target.display: A set of rules under which this content was created
target.comment: R4B `Binary.implicitRules` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.implicitRules`
R4B `Binary.language` maps as RelatedTo to R5 `Binary.language` - language made the binding required (from Preferred) for http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/all-languages|5.0.0
R4B `Binary.meta` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.meta`

element.display: Identifies another resource to use as proxy when enforcing access control

target.display: Identifies another resource to use as proxy when enforcing access control
target.comment: R4B `Binary.securityContext` maps as Equivalent to R5 `Binary.securityContext`
